<subSubSection id="C32A18FC286CFFCCFF20876FE4656A7A" lastPageId="43" lastPageNumber="294" pageId="38" pageNumber="289" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8F4B77286CFFC1FF20876FE2A46CEC" blockId="38.[151,1436,1837,2010]" pageId="38" pageNumber="289">
<emphasis id="B9449765286CFFC1FF20876FE02F6C7C" bold="true" box="[151,266,1837,1862]" pageId="38" pageNumber="289">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The habitus of the type-species of the new genus is unique within the whole tribe. The pale greyishbrown forewing lacks all but one crosslines except the oblique, straight, pale, but well visible brownish postmedial line. The other markings of the wing are conspicuous blackish patches on the basal and medial part of the costa, an oblique row of three dots in the terminal area and a larger patch at the middle of the ventral margin. The hindwing venation is typically „quadrifine”, with the M 
<number id="3DF85950286CFFC1FD21878EE3BB6CE0" box="[662,670,1996,2010]" pageId="38" pageNumber="289" value="3.0">3</number>
+CuA 
<number id="3DF85950286CFFC1FD55878EE3CF6CE0" box="[738,746,1996,2010]" pageId="38" pageNumber="289" value="1.0">1</number>
long stalked.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF4F1BFF286DFFC0FF208797E2006CD1" box="[151,805,2005,2027]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/240610/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="290" targetBox="[175,1414,205,1965]" targetPageId="39">
